<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1233,2032]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,515,1658,1684]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Habitat and Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van de Vijver &amp; Zidarova" authorityYear="2011" box="[552,1054,1658,1684]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="borealis" variety="pseudolanceolata">
<emphasis box="[552,784,1659,1684]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Pinnularia borealis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[847,1054,1659,1684]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">pseudolanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rare on Livingston Island. A large population was observed in a large, circumneutral (pH 7.3) shallow pool on Byers Peninsula with low specific conductance values (&lt;100 µS/cm) surrounded by fellfields and moss vegetations, growing into the water. Smaller populations were observed on Hurd Peninsula, situated in the southern part of Livingston Island (recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zidarova, R." box="[398,576,1813,1839]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" pagination="19 - 35" refId="ref8253" refString="Zidarova, R. (2008) Algae from Livingston Island (S Shetland Islands): a checklist. Phytologica Balcanica 14: 19 - 35." type="journal article" year="2008">Zidarova 2008</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[620,827,1813,1839]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="undefined-A">
<emphasis box="[620,752,1813,1838]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Pinnularia</emphasis>
sp. A
</taxonomicName>
) in a wide variety of samples, mainly on soil and mosses (both dry and semi-wet), rarely in pools, and always in low numbers. One population of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van de Vijver &amp; Zidarova" authorityYear="2011" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="borealis" variety="pseudolanceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Pinnularia borealis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[313,529,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">pseudolanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed on James Ross Island (Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová, unpubl. results).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1233,2032]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,333,1967,1993]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The varietal epithet refers to the resemblance to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hustedt" authorityName="Hustedt" authorityYear="1934" box="[971,1391,1968,1994]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="borealis" variety="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[971,1099,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">P. borealis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1165,1288,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">lanceolata</emphasis>
Hustedt
</taxonomicName>
(in Schmidt 
<emphasis box="[256,315,2007,2032]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">et al.</emphasis>
1934: pl. 388, fig. 16–17).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,642]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,364,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Observations</emphasis>
:—There are hardly any lanceolate taxa belonging to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1058,1169,152,177]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="section" section="Distantes">
<emphasis box="[1058,1169,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Distantes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Boye-Petersen described a 
<taxonomicName authority="Boye-Petersen (1928: 402)" authorityName="Boye-Petersen" authorityPageNumber="402" authorityYear="1928" box="[294,907,190,216]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" form="lanceolata" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="form" species="borealis">
<emphasis box="[294,420,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">P. borealis</emphasis>
f. 
<emphasis box="[453,578,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">lanceolata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boye-Petersen, J." box="[587,907,190,216]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" pagination="325 - 447" refId="ref6623" refString="Boye-Petersen, J. (1928) The aerial algae of Iceland. In: Rosenvinge, L. K. &amp; Warming, E. (eds.), The Botany of Iceland, vol. 2, part 2, no. 8. J. Frimodt, Kobenhavn, pp. 325 - 447." type="book chapter" year="1928">Boye-Petersen (1928: 402)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[981,1068,190,216]" name="Iceland" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Iceland</collectingCountry>
but it is wider than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van de Vijver &amp; Zidarova" authorityYear="2011" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="borealis" variety="pseudolanceolata">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">P. borealis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[203,412,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">pseudolanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a more broadly lanceolate valve outline (Table 1). Hustedt described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boye-Petersen" authorityYear="1928" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="borealis" variety="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">P. borealis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[205,335,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Schwarzsee in Davos but the description was based on only 
<specimenCount box="[1211,1392,268,294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
(in Schmidt 
<emphasis box="[258,317,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
1934: pl. 388, fig. 16–17). 
<bibRefCitation author="Krammer, K." box="[648,841,306,332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" refId="ref7150" refString="Krammer, K. (2000) The genus Pinnularia. In: H. Lange-Bertalot (ed.), Diatoms of Europe, Diatoms of the European Inland waters and comparable habitats. A. R. G. Gantner Verlag K. G., 1: 703 pp." type="book" year="2000">Krammer (2000</bibRefCitation>
, 25) stated that “only single specimens have been found” and that more information is necessary to understand the correct identity of the species. Compared to valves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boye-Petersen" authorityYear="1928" box="[273,598,384,410]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="borealis" variety="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[273,403,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">P. borealis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[468,598,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Simonsen, R." box="[815,1019,384,410]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" refId="ref7589" refString="Simonsen, R. (1987) Atlas and Catalogue of the Diatom Types of Friedrich Hustedt, 3 vols. J. Cramer Berlin-Stuttgart." type="book" year="1987">Simonsen (1987</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 249, figs 4–7, illustrations of Husetdt’s 
<typeStatus box="[268,318,422,448]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">type</typeStatus>
specimens), the Livingston populations have a higher number of striae (6–8 vs. 
<quantity box="[1251,1295,422,448]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[1302,1379,422,448]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
) and a lower valve width (
<quantity box="[415,542,461,487]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12 µm</quantity>
for Hustedt’s specimens vs. 
<quantity box="[902,1044,461,487]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="7.5">7.5–9.5 µm</quantity>
for specimens from Livingston Island) (Table 1). 
<taxonomicName authority="Manguin" authorityName="Manguin" authorityYear="1952" box="[369,866,500,526]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="borealis" variety="undata">
<emphasis box="[369,605,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Pinnularia borealis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[666,749,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">undata</emphasis>
Manguin
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bourrelly, P. &amp; Manguin, E." box="[916,1298,500,526]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" refId="ref6554" refString="Bourrelly, P. &amp; Manguin, E. (1952) Algues d'eau douce de la Guadeloupe et dependances. Centre Natural de Recherches Scientifiques, Paris, 281 pp." type="book" year="1952">Bourrelly &amp; Manguin 1952: 80</bibRefCitation>
), described from Guadeloupe, is also wider (
<quantity box="[538,640,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 µm</quantity>
) with a lower number of striae (
<quantity box="[1022,1068,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[1076,1157,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
). In 
<bibRefCitation author="Frenguelli, J." box="[1210,1436,538,564]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" pagination="73 - 219" refId="ref6835" refString="Frenguelli, J. (1942) Diatomeas del Neuquen (Patagonia). Revista del Museo de la Plata, nueva serie, Seccion Botanica 5: 73 - 219." type="journal article" year="1942">Frenguelli’s (1942)</bibRefCitation>
study, he illustrates several lanceolate valves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1843" box="[739,868,577,602]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis box="[739,868,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">P. borealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but identifies them all as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1843" box="[1186,1315,577,602]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis box="[1186,1315,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">P. borealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1323,1358,577,603]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Other lanceolate 
<taxonomicName box="[277,388,616,641]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="section" section="Distantes">
<emphasis box="[277,388,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Distantes</emphasis>
